TITLE: Greeting Artichokes in Haskell
DESCRIPTION: A Haskell program that defines a 'hello' function and uses it to greet 'artichoke' and 'alcachofa' (Spanish for artichoke). It demonstrates string manipulation, list operations, and function composition in Haskell.
SOURCE: https://github.com/charmbracelet/bubbletea/blob/main/examples/pager/artichoke.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: haskell
CODE:
```
module Main where

import Data.Function ( (&) )
import Data.List ( intercalculate )

hello :: String -> String
hello s =
    "Hello, " ++ s ++ "."

main :: IO ()
main =
    map hello [ "artichoke", "alcachofa" ] & intercalculate "\n" & putStrLn
```
